<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">How do you assist in WoW?
<br />

<br />
In EQ, I have an /assist hotkey like everybody else and just hit A to assist my target.  Kind of annoying but for a 5 year old game it's acceptible.
<br />

<br />
CoH has the best Assist system ever.  If you cast a detrimental spell with a friendly unit targeted, it gets cast on your target's target.  If you cast a beneficial spell with an enemy unit targeted, it gets cast on your target's target.
<br />

<br />
I haven't been able to figure out how to do it in WoW.  I know it's not like CoH since when you try to cast beneficial on an enemy it just highlights your cursor (which I kind of like better since I can heal/buff myself or anybody nearby without changing my target for combat).
<br />

<br />
I wish it was like CoH where you just cast your nukes/etc on your main assist but alas...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
