<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="88240"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#11:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Max of Tunare</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=88240#88240"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Thu Dec 02, 2004 3:58 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I have to assume that he means right-click on a target. It targets and sets attack on. And if you have click-move turned on it'll also run you to the location of the target (at least where it was when you clicked it).
<br />

<br />
The tab key will cycle targets, I believe - along with selecting the closest target the first time.
<br />

<br />
In addition, the folowing work:
<br />

<br />
/assist &lt;name&gt;
<br />
/target &lt;name&gt;
<br />

<br />
You can also alt-&lt;hotkey&gt; to cast the &lt;hotkeyed&gt; spell on yourself. Click the F1-F5 key twice to target a pet, and (I think) shift (or alt)-Fx to target the pet.
<br />

<br />
I think it was also mentioned that you can press a hotkey for a benficial spell, like a heal, with a agro mob targeted and you're now primed to cast that heal on a friend. Click their Fx key and it'll cast the spell on them *without changing the target*. Very cool in my opinion.
<br />

<br />
Clicking both the left and right mouse buttons cause you to run. Let up on either and you stop. Very handy for swimming since you can control up-down left-right with the mouse also.
<br />

<br />
The one thing I've found with the text in hotkeys is that if my druid is shapeshifted I have to hit a hotkey to which the shapeshift key is bound. I can't put the 'cast' of the shapeshift back into druid form in a macro because it tells me that I can't cast while shapeshifted. I wanted to do this so that I could have a hotkey that would shift me out of bearform, target me and cast a heal spell. I have to settle for 2 hotkeys.
<br />

<br />
You can also hit ctrl-F1 to shift into and out of bearform, and ctrl-F2 to shift into/out of aquatic form.
<br />

<br />
The ctrl-Fx key also works for abilities other classes have that add icons above the hotkey bar.
<br />

<br />
You can also cast or use an ability directly from the spellbook, it doesn't need to be bound to a key, and the only penalty - as far as I can see - is the time spent *finding* it in the book.
<br />

<br />
I bound the ctrl-left arrow and ctrl-right arrow to strafe left and strafe right, and when I use these and let up on the ctrl key it continues strafing rather than start turning as it does in EQ.
<br />

<br />
I suggest you hit Esc and check out key bindings. Some very interesting functions available.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
